Project Explanation: AI Sentiment Analysis + Trend Prediction System

 What the project is
This project is an AI-powered system that analyzes people’s opinions in text (like social media posts, comments, or reviews) and then:


Detects the sentiment (positive, negative, or neutral)


Tracks how opinions change over time


Uses AI to predict future trends in public opinion


In simple words:
👉 It reads what people write, understands their feelings, and predicts what might happen next.

⚙️ How it works (simple breakdown)
1. Data Input
The system takes text data such as:


Social media comments


Product reviews


News reactions


Example:

“I really love this product”
“This is getting worse every day”


2. Sentiment Analysis (AI part)
The AI model reads the text and decides:


😊 Positive


😐 Neutral


😠 Negative


It does this using Natural Language Processing (NLP), which allows computers to understand human language.

3. Trend Tracking
The system stores sentiment results over time and creates a pattern like:


Day 1 → mostly positive


Day 2 → mixed


Day 3 → mostly negative


This shows how public opinion is changing.

4. Prediction (Machine Learning)
The system uses simple machine learning (like regression) to:
👉 Predict future sentiment trends
Example:


“Negative opinions are increasing → likely to continue tomorrow”



📊 Output
The system shows:


Sentiment score


Graph of changes over time


Future prediction



